# Privacy Policy

**Last updated:** 6 April 2026

This Privacy Policy describes how this app ("the App") collects, uses, and handles your information.

---

## 1. Information We Collect

The App uses **Firebase Analytics** to collect anonymous usage data, including:

- App interactions (screen views, button taps, session duration)
- Device type and operating system version
- App version
- Anonymous installation ID (not linked to your identity)

We do **not** collect your name, email address, location, or any personally identifiable information.

---

## 2. How We Use Your Information

The information collected is used solely for:

- Understanding how users interact with the App
- Improving app performance and user experience
- Identifying and fixing crashes or bugs

---

## 3. Third-Party Services

The App uses the following third-party service:

- **Firebase Analytics** (Google LLC) — for anonymous usage analytics. See [Google's Privacy Policy](https://policies.google.com/privacy) for details.

---

## 4. Data Retention

Anonymous analytics data is retained in accordance with Google Firebase's standard data retention policies. No personal data is stored by the App on external servers.

---

## 5. Children's Privacy

The App does not knowingly collect any information from children under the age of 13. If you believe your child has provided information through the App, please contact us and we will take steps to remove it.

---

## 6. Your Rights (Australian Privacy Act 1988)

Under the **Australian Privacy Act 1988**, you have the right to:

- Request access to information held about you
- Request correction of inaccurate information
- Lodge a complaint with the [Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC)](https://www.oaic.gov.au)

As the App does not collect personally identifiable information, there is generally no personal data to access or correct.

---

## 7. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected with an updated date at the top of this page. Continued use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

